{
  "topicId": "m6-t1",
  "title": "Asking About Directions in Egyptian Arabic",
  "dialect": "egyptian-arabic",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Getting Attention Politely: Excuse Me",
          "arabic": "لفت الانتباه بلطف: لو سمحت"
        },
        "text": "Before asking for directions, it's polite to get someone's attention. In Egyptian Arabic, you can use 'لو سمحت' which means 'Excuse me' or 'Please'. It's versatile and can be used for both males and females.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "لو سمحت.",
            "english": "Excuse me (to get attention).",
            "transliteration": "Law samaḥt."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "لو سمحت، ممكن تساعدني؟",
            "english": "Excuse me, can you help me?",
            "transliteration": "Law samaḥt, mumkin tesa'edny?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'Where is...?'",
          "arabic": "السؤال عن 'أين...؟'"
        },
        "text": "The most direct way to ask 'Where is...?' in Egyptian Arabic is 'فين...؟' (feen...?). You simply add the name of the place after it.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "فين؟",
            "english": "Where?",
            "transliteration": "Feen?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "فين المستشفى؟",
            "english": "Where is the hospital?",
            "transliteration": "Feen el mostashfa?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Common Places: Bank, Station, Museum",
          "arabic": "أماكن شائعة: بنك، محطة، متحف"
        },
        "text": "Let's learn some common places you might ask for. Remember to use the definite article 'ال' (el-) before the noun.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "البنك",
            "english": "The bank",
            "transliteration": "El bank"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "المحطة",
            "english": "The station (train/bus)",
            "transliteration": "El maḥaṭṭa"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "المتحف",
            "english": "The museum",
            "transliteration": "El matḥaf"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
