    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Going Straight",
          "arabic": "الإتجاه إلى الأمام"
        },
        "text": "When someone tells you to go straight, they will use phrases like 'إمشي طوالي' or 'إمشي على طول'. Both mean 'walk straight' or 'go straight on'. 'إمشي' is the imperative for 'walk' (to a male). For a female, it would be 'إمشيي'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "إمشي طوالي.",
            "english": "Go straight.",
            "transliteration": "Emshy ṭawaly."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "إمشي على طول.",
            "english": "Keep walking straight.",
            "transliteration": "Emshy 'ala ṭool."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Turning Right",
          "arabic": "الإتجاه يميناً"
        },
        "text": "To tell someone to turn right, you'll hear 'لف يمين' or 'إحود يمين'. 'لف' means 'turn' and 'إحود' means 'turn/veer' (used more for vehicles but also for people). 'يمين' means 'right'. For a female, it would be 'لفي يمين' or 'إحودي يمين'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "لف يمين.",
            "english": "Turn right.",
            "transliteration": "Liff yemeen."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "إحود يمين.",
            "english": "Turn right (alternative).",
            "transliteration": "Eḥwid yemeen."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Turning Left",
          "arabic": "الإتجاه يساراً"
        },
        "text": "Similar to turning right, to tell someone to turn left, you'll hear 'لف شمال' or 'إحود شمال'. 'شمال' means 'left'. For a female, it's 'لفي شمال' or 'إحودي شمال'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "لف شمال.",
            "english": "Turn left.",
            "transliteration": "Liff shemal."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "إحود شمال.",
            "english": "Turn left (alternative).",
            "transliteration": "Eḥwid shemal."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "إمشي طوالي، بعدين لف يمين.",
        "english": "Go straight, then turn right.",
        "transliteration": "Emshy ṭawaly, ba'deen liff yemeen."
      },
      "context": "Combining 'go straight' with 'turn right'."
    },
