    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Far / Close",
          "arabic": "بعيد / قريب"
        },
        "text": "Understanding if a place is 'far' or 'close' is crucial. 'بعيد' (ba'eed) means 'far' and 'قريب' (ʾareeb) means 'close'. These are adjectives and can change slightly for female nouns, but in common speech for locations, they often remain masculine or are understood.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هو بعيد من هنا.",
            "english": "It's far from here.",
            "transliteration": "Howa ba'eed men hena."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هي قريبة من هنا.",
            "english": "It's close from here.",
            "transliteration": "Heyya 'areeba men hena."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Walk a Bit / A Little While",
          "arabic": "إمشي شوية / حتة"
        },
        "text": "Often directions involve walking for a short distance. 'إمشي شوية' (emshy showaya) means 'walk a bit/a little' and 'إمشي حتة' (emshy ḥetta) means 'walk a piece/a short distance'. Both imply walking for a short while.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "إمشي شوية طوالي.",
            "english": "Walk a bit straight.",
            "transliteration": "Emshy showaya ṭawaly."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بعد ما تلف يمين، إمشي حتة.",
            "english": "After you turn right, walk a short distance.",
            "transliteration": "Ba'd ma teliff yemeen, emshy ḥetta."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Crossing the Street",
          "arabic": "عبور الشارع"
        },
        "text": "If you need to cross a street, the phrase 'عدّي الشارع' ('addy esh-shara') is used. 'عدّي' (to a male) is the imperative for 'cross'. For a female, it's 'عدّيِ'. 'الشارع' is 'the street'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "إمشي طوالي وعدّي الشارع.",
            "english": "Go straight and cross the street.",
            "transliteration": "Emshy ṭawaly w 'addy esh-shara'."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "المحطة بعد ما تعدّي الشارع.",
            "english": "The station is after you cross the street.",
            "transliteration": "El maḥaṭṭa ba'd ma te'addy esh-shara'."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
